cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.DS 

This paper discusses a Sybil attack on social location-based services, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack involves manipulating social navigation systems, which can be considered a form of social computing (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of fake GPS reports involves data and information management (cs.CY), and the techniques for preventing the attack may involve algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
